Use positive path bounds for display list visibility test. Skia does not have a consistent policy for handling "inverted" shapes (rects  rrects  ovals): some Skia APIs check or flip the bounds  some do not. In general  Skia treats inverted shapes as undefined behavior and doesn't want to commit to an explicit contract for handling them. Further  this undefined behavior is actually soon going to change (to different undefined behavior; parent bug is skbug.com/454646294).  One instance where reliance on this undefined Skia behavior impacts flutter is mentioned in https://github.com/flutter/engine/pull/42556. This PR applies the same fix to drawPath()  removing its dependence on undefined Skia behavior.  <!-- Thanks for filing a pull request! Reviewers are typically assigned within a week of filing a request. To learn more about code review  see our documentation on Tree Hygiene: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/main/docs/contributing/Tree-hygiene.md -->  *Replace this paragraph with a description of what this PR is changing or a

Ensure positive rects in DlPath factory methods Skia does not have a consistent policy for handling "inverted" shapes (rects  rrects  ovals): some Skia APIs check or flip the bounds  some do not. In general  Skia treats inverted shapes as undefined behavior and doesn't want to commit to an explicit contract for handling them. Further  this undefined behavior is actually soon going to change (to different undefined behavior; parent bug is skbug.com/454646294).  One instance where reliance on this undefined Skia behavior impacts flutter is mentioned in https://github.com/flutter/engine/pull/42556.  This PR applies a normalization to DlPaths created via factory methods that consume a DlRect  ensuring that the path geometry created from the input rects is not inverted.  <!-- Thanks for filing a pull request! Reviewers are typically assigned within a week of filing a request. To learn more about code review  see our documentation on Tree Hygiene: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/main/docs/contributing/Tree-hygiene.md -->

Add framework-side hitTestBehavior support to Semantics This is a reland of #177570  which was reverted in #178744 due to test failures.
The original PR introduced `hitTestBehavior` to the semantics framework but incorrectly applied `opaque` behavior to `ModalRoute`  which blocked platform views from receiving pointer events.
Instead of making the entire modal opaque  we:
1. Keep `ModalRoute` without explicit `hitTestBehavior` (defaults to `defer`)
2. Make only the dialog/sheet content opaque (blocks clicks to barrier)
3. Platform views remain clickable because they're outside the opaque content boundary
Fixes #149001
Original PR: #177570
Revert: #178744

✨ Add `flutter generate` command for scaffolding widgets and screens ## Description
closes #179059

This PR introduces a new `flutter generate` command that allows developers to quickly scaffold Flutter widgets and screens from the command line  similar to Angular's `ng generate` command. This feature significantly improves developer productivity by eliminating the need to manually create files through the IDE file explorer.
## Motivation
When building Flutter applications  developers frequently need to create new widgets and screens. The current workflow typically involves:
1. Using the mouse to navigate the file explorer in VS Code
2. Right-clicking to create a new file
3. Typing the filename
4. Writing boilerplate code manually

This is time-consuming and breaks the flow of development. Having built applications with Angular (another Google open-source project)  I found the `ng generate` command extremely helpful  and I believe Flutter developers would benefit from similar functionality.

Remove semantics geometry shortcircuit Fixes https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/173097

The semantics flush is ~200 μs slower with the shortcuircut removed  + #177477 (which reduces the time increase by ~ 100 μs  from 876 μs to 773 μs) I tried to introduce caching in [a different patch](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/compare/master...LongCatIsLooong:semantics-geometry?expand=1) but that patch is more risky and still needs a cleanup.

773 μs doesn't seem bad considering there were little to no geometry updates between frames before the fix. Introducing cache currently only improves `Semantics.ensureGeometry` by less than 100 μs and is much more risky / harder to ensure the correctness.

Add an assert message when OverlayEntry.remove is called twice ## Description  This PR adds an assert message to help users understand the error occuring when `OverlayEntry.remove` is called twice. It also adds a comment about calling dispose after removal as this is mandatory since github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/102794.  ## Related Issue  Fixes ["Failed assertion: line 207 pos 12: '_overlay != null': is not true" when trying to remove a non null overlayEntry](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/145466)  Related external issue: https://github.com/LanarsInc/top-snackbar-flutter/issues/80  ## Tests  - Adds 1 test.

Dynamically set MinimumOSVersion in App.framework Currently  the MinimumOSVersion in App.framework/Info.plist is sourced from a static template file created during flutter create. This value can become out of sync with the -miphoneos-version-min flag used to compile the App.framework binary  especially after a Flutter SDK upgrade. This mismatch can lead to App Store submission warnings or rejections.
This change fixes the issue by making the build process the single source of truth for the MinimumOSVersion.

Add SliverIndexedVariedExtentList to support jumpToIndex Related: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/12319 https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/81005

This PR adds a new sliver named `SliverIndexedVariedExtentList` which takes an `itemExtentBuilder`  an `anchor` index and an `indexedScrollController` which has `jumpToIndex` and `animateToIndex` methods. There is also an `itemPositionsListener` that can listen to index positions on the viewport.

I think this is a good idea in general but I'm hoping to get some feedback on the API early as mentioned in the [guide](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/master/docs/contributing/Tree-hygiene.md#when).

At a high level this basically follows the idea by @gaaclarke in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/12319#issuecomment-546038123. Since Flutter viewports deal in pixel offsets  if we want to jump to an index we need to be able to convert indices to offsets. This functionality was actually added in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/131393 to support an `itemExtentB
